note bottom of generation_job
  storybook_id is NOT a foreign key.
  A job may fail before any storybook
  row exists; a hard FK would block
  inserting the failure record.
  Application layer verifies the
  storybook row exists when reading
  this field.
end note

note bottom of reading_state
  Composite FK (storybook_id, version)
  references storybook_version (pk).
  Prevents saving state for a version
  that does not exist.
end note

note bottom of user_t
  Several tables carry a pure-attribution
  FK to user.id, annotated inline on the
  owning column but not drawn as an arrow
  here (to keep the graph legible):
  series.created_by, storybook.created_by,
  storybook_version.approved_by,
  storybook_assignment.assigned_by,
  concept.created_by, story_request.reviewed_by,
  moderation_threshold.updated_by,
  moderation_threshold_audit.changed_by (NOT NULL),
  moderation_setting.updated_by,
  provider_model_allowlist.created_by/updated_by,
  provider_model_allowlist_audit.changed_by (NOT NULL),
  family_connection.created_by,
  family_connection.consented_by_viewer_user_id,
  family_connection.consented_by_sharer_user_id,
  kid_flag.resolved_by,
  pipeline_event.actor_id (NULL iff actor_role='system').
end note

note bottom of device_grant
  ADR-014: a guardian-minted, durable (90-day,
  revocable) family-scoped authorization. The
  signed token (HS256, aud cyo-device-grant) is
  never stored; only its jti and mint metadata
  are. jti is UNIQUE so the revocation lookup
  (checked online only) is unambiguous.
  Table name is singular (device_grant); the
  REST surface is plural (/v1/device-grants).
end note

note bottom of pipeline_event
  WS-D append-only lifecycle log (spec
  decision D1): written from the same
  transaction as the transition it
  records; a DB trigger blocks UPDATE/
  DELETE. entity_type/entity_id together
  identify the row the event describes
  (e.g. entity_type='story_request',
  entity_id=<uuid>). Not a foreign key:
  entity_type varies per row, so no
  single-table FK target applies.
end note

@enduml
